<font color="#FF0000">THE WAR I SAW</font><br>
<tt>Tue Feb 18 22:50:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
War is a word in a history book. War is also what those who<br>
got to participate get to refer to their experience by.<br><br>
If you want to talk about the book war, fine. That's a<br>
different animal. If you want to talk about what a War is<br>
to those that participate, that's another.<br><br>
When you read about &quot;my personal war&quot;, then you get to the<br>
gist of what it does to people. If you wish to discuss what<br>
the series of events the &quot;War&quot; was, read history as written<br>
by &quot;those&quot; who know.<br><br>
I got a pretty good idea what War is to those who get to <br>
play the game. It's about fear. A fear that cannot be<br>
measured on any scale. Fear is killing a human. It takes<br>
you right to the greatest terror we all had since childhood.<br>
I was most frightened when someone tried to kill me, and <br>
most of all when I succeeded in killing them. That brought<br>
my reality to a head. When you look down on someone you<br>
killed when you are just a soldier, that is when you are<br>
most afraid. The dead guy below you is the bottom line just<br>
became your reality. It probably wasn't that way until then.<br><br>
That's the horror of it. It's personal. Can't get that out<br>
of the formula. As General Patton said &quot;Make the other<br>
fucker die for his country.&quot;<br><br>
Sad, Sad, Sad. But that's the way is was and is.<br><br>
I don't give humans that much credit for being able to be<br>
different. As for God, well he let me get a good glimpse of<br>
the nobility of Man. We ain't got none. It's only something<br>
we strive to acheive. Sorry to say this to my religious<br>
pals, but their ain't no God. I don't mean to offend. The<br>
God I got to see after years of being raised in religon,<br>
was our lack of a genetic moral ethic. It only comes from<br>
our society. And that's no certainty. No Society can escape<br>
it. We can do OK. But that's about it.<br><br>
No peace like a cynic's peace.<br><br>

<p><code>-- carnival@ont.com  (JJ the Boonirat) </code><p>


